onial theory and security studies, Julius Heise presents a theory-driven history of Togoland's path to independence, offering a crucial lesson for international statebuilding efforts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aAdministration. 4aGlobalization. 4aInternational Relations. 4aPolitical Science. 4aPolitics. 4aPostcolonialism. 4aSecurity. 4aState. 4aStatebuilding. 4aTrusteeship. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aAdministration.  aGlobalization.  aInternational Relations.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitics.  aPostcolonialism.  aSecurity.  aState.  aStatebuilding.  aTrusteeship.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839473061?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839473061zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839473061/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA